<TITLE> PM urges people to adjust to DST </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 19 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has urged people to adjust to Daylight Saving Time being introduced to make the maximum use of limited energy resources. She opened the cover of a replica watch and released a special commemorative stamp at her Jamuna residence at 10:44pm on Friday, minutes before clocks were to be moved an hour ahead from 11pm. The energy-starved nation is introducing Daylight Saving Time for 'an extra hour of daylight' to save power. She acknowledged power crisis and said her administration was doing everything to ease the meance plaguing the peole and the economy. A cabinet meeting chaired by Hasina on June 1 decided the move. Hasina had promised before the Dec 29 general elections to address the power crisis. bdnew
